description: Did you know that the first time anyone ever saw Michael Jordan wearing Air Jordan 1 sneakers was in a 1985 Nike poster? description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Bred Toe’ is a brand new take on a classic design. This Chicago Bulls-inspired colorway is a perfect combination of the ‘Bred’ and ‘Black Toe’ editions of the Air Jordan 1. It is constructed with premium leather and high-quality materials, making it a durable and long lasting shoe. The Swoosh on the quarter panel is black, with contrasting red pops on the toe box, heel, collar, and outsole. This shoe stays true to its OG 1985 roots, with Nike Air branding on the tongue tag and sockliner. The ‘Bred Toe’ is a must-have for any Air Jordan fan.

Released alongside a small capsule collection of clothing, the Nike Supreme x Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Desert Camo' is a must-have for any fan of either brand.

title: Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Taxi' 2013  130690-125
description: The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Taxi' 2013 is a true classic sneaker. First released in 1996, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Taxi' 2013 is based on the OG white/black colorway worn by Michael Jordan himself during the 1996-97 NBA regular season. The sneaker features beautiful metallic gold eyelets and a black outsole with a carbon fiber shank that references the black and yellow of NYC Taxi cabs. The 'Taxi' was first retroed in 2008 as part of Nike's Countdown Collection, and was also given the low-top treatment in 2011. If you're a true sneakerhead, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Taxi' 2013 is a must-have in your collection!

title: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Hall of Fame'  136064-116
description:
When it comes to iconic sneakers, it doesn't get much more legendary than the Air Jordan 3 Retro. First released in 2006 in support of Hurricane Katrina relief efforts, this shoe is making a comeback today to honor both Michael Jordan's legacy in this humanitarian effort and his 2009 inclusion in the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame.

Featuring a white leather upper with cement grey and elephant print details, black and Fire Red accents, and the iconic Jumpman logo on the heel, this sneaker is a true classic. Whether you're a basketball fan or just a fan of great sneakers, the Air Jordan 3 Retro is a must-have for any collection. Order yours today and help support a great cause!

title: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Fire Red' 2013  136064-120
description: If you're a fan of the Chicago Bulls, then you need to get your hands on a pair of Air Jordan 3 Retro "Fire Red" 2013. These sneakers are one of four OG colorways of the silhouette and they are sure to make you stand out from the rest. The white tumbled and smooth leather upper is complemented by the signature elephant print in black, while the Fire Red on the midsole, ankle and branding completes the look. The Jumpman on the heel separates it from the launch colorway, making it a must-have for any collection.

title: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Mocha' 2018  136064-122
description: Bringing back the color scheme first released in 2001, the Nike Air Jordan 3 Retro "Mocha" complements the white tumbled leather upper with brown elephant print accents. The brown color story is extended to the outsole and Jumpman logo at the heel.

title: Air Jordan 12 Retro 'University Gold'  151186-070

The perfect addition to your sneaker rotation, this style is sure to turn heads no matter where you go.

The sneaker features premium materials and authentic details, making it a must-have for any true Jordan fan.

title: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Cement' 2011  136064-010
description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro is one of the most popular sneakers of all time. Originally released in 1988, the sneaker was designed by the legendary Tinker Hatfield and is recognized for its iconic elephant print detailing. The Air Jordan 3 Retro has been released several times since its initial release, but this 2011 version is one of the most popular iterations. This retro sneaker features the classic black and cement grey colorway with Jumpman branding on the tongue and heel. The Air Jordan 3 Retro is a must-have for any sneaker collection and is perfect for everyday wear.

The Air Jordan 1 KO, also known as the AJKO, debuted back in 1986. The “KO” is believed to stand for “knock-off” as in, a cheaper version of the original Air Jordan 1 High. Dressed in a Black, Sail, and Medium Grey color scheme nodding back to the OG “Shadow” release. This offering of the Air Jordan 1 KO Low comes constricted in a full Black and Grey canvas base with Grey suede Swooshes and leather heel overlay. Other details includes “Nike” logos on the tongue tags and insole with Black Wings embroidery on the heels. Black nylon tongues, sizing stamped on the inner lining atop an aged midsole and Black rubber outsole completes the design.

title: Air Jordan 12 Utility 'Grind'  DM5204-006
description: Looking for a pair of shoes that are both stylish and sustainable? Look no further than the Air Jordan 12 Retro Utility GS "Grind"! These grade-school sneakers are constructed with tumbled leather and nubuck, finished in black with stitched detailing and Bright Crimson accents. A heel pull-loop makes them easy to put on and take off, while full-length Zoom Air cushioning provides a comfortable ride. And best of all, they feature Nike Grind rubber outsoles made from recycled material - perfect for the eco-conscious shopper. Whether you're hitting the court or just running errands, the Air Jordan 12 Retro Utility GS "Grind" has you covered in style!

description:
The Air Jordan 1 KO, also known as the AJKO, debuted back in 1986. The “KO” is believed to stand for “knock-off” as in, a cheaper version of the original Air Jordan 1 High. Dressed in a Black, Sail, and Medium Grey color scheme nodding back to the OG “Shadow” release. This offering of the Air Jordan 1 KO Low comes constricted in a full Black and Grey canvas base with Grey suede Swooshes and leather heel overlay. Other details includes “Nike” logos on the tongue tags and insole with Black Wings embroidery on the heels. Black nylon tongues, sizing stamped on the inner lining atop an aged midsole and Black rubber outsole completes the design.

description: Looking for a shoe that's as cool as it is stylish? Look no further than the Air Jordan 1 Mid Motorsport BP. This kids-exclusive release is inspired by Michael Jordan's love of auto racing, and it shows in the vibrant hues and unique details. The upper is made from diamond-textured white synthetic leather, with nubby textures on the forefoot and heel overlay. The Swoosh and collar flap are done in matching gold, with a red Wings logo on the lateral side. Additional branding elements include '23' imprinted on the forefoot and a checkerboard Jordan decal atop the heel.The durable rubber cupsole provides lasting comfort and style.

The forefoot and heel overlays are in Gym Red and University Gold, while the lateral side features the ‘23’ stamp. The back heel has a checkerboard Jordan decal, and the whole sneaker sits on a standard rubber cupsole. Your little one will love showing off this stylish new sneaker!
